---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
---

<ProjectLayout
  title="Square: Public Web Design System"
  year="2020–2023"
  tags={['Design Systems', 'CSS', 'Architecture']}
  description="A flexible and extensible web design system for Square's evolving visual identity — spanning marketing, product, and developer tooling."
  nextSlug="square-atlanta"
  nextTitle="The Future Is Built in Atlanta"
>

  <div class="cs-section">
    <span class="cs-label">Overview</span>
    <div class="cs-body">
      <p>
        As a Design Technologist at Block, I contributed to the public-facing web design system that underpinned Square's marketing and product web presence. The system needed to flex across a rapidly evolving brand while remaining stable enough for teams across the company to ship confidently.
      </p>
      <p>
        Work spanned <strong>component architecture</strong>, <strong>design token systems</strong>, and close collaboration with designers to close the gap between intent and implementation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="cs-divider" />

  <div class="cs-section">
    <span class="cs-label">Problem</span>
    <div class="cs-body">
      <p>
        Square's web presence had grown organically across teams — inconsistent markup patterns, duplicated components, and no shared source of truth. Brand updates required touching dozens of isolated codebases.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="cs-divider" />

  <div class="cs-section">
    <span class="cs-label">Solution</span>
    <div class="cs-body">
      <p>
        Built a modular, token-driven component library with clear extension points — allowing teams to adopt the system without being locked into it. Authored documentation and contributed to the processes that defined how the Design Technologist role operated at Block.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="cs-divider" />

  <div class="cs-section">
    <span class="cs-label">Tech stack</span>
    <div class="cs-body">
      <ul class="cs-stack">
        <li>CSS Custom Properties</li>
        <li>Design Tokens</li>
        <li>Svelte</li>
        <li>Figma</li>
        <li>Storybook</li>
        <li>Headless CMS</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

</ProjectLayout>
